description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and motivated applicant to join our ward team to provide admin support to our ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;F6 is a cardiothoracic surgery ward caring for patients undergoing cardiac, aortic &amp; thoracic surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a strong team work ethic, sense of accountability, accompanied by an ability to work under pressure at times. This post is open to entrants with the right attributes to enhance a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be based on ward F6, at Wythenshawe Hospital. The successful candidate will work 30hrs a week Monday - Friday, hours will be worked 7am to 6pm in 10 hour shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be highly organised and have excellent communication and customer service skills. You will provide a complete range of reception and administrative services including data input. You will liaise with all levels of clinical and administrative staff and welcome all patients and visitors to the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is varied, interesting and challenging. You must enjoy working as part of a team as well as being able to use your own initiative. You will be flexible and able to prioritise your own workload. A friendly personality and a mature, confident outlook are key to this role as well as a conscientious and pro-active approach. Experience in a similar position is an advantage but is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAdele BrearleyJob titleF6 Ward ManagerEmail addressadele.brearley@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 291 2566Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
